annotations.title: What Perseverance, NASA's New Mars Rover, Will Be Doing in its Years on the Red Planet
NASA's Mars helicopter takes flight as first aircraft piloted on another planet

content.text:
- **Perseverance Rover Landing (Feb. 18, 2021):** NASA’s Perseverance rover touched down in Mars’ Jezero Crater, marking a major milestone in Mars exploration. The mission’s goals include searching for signs of ancient microbial life in the once-wet crater and collecting rock samples for a future return to Earth ([time.com](https://time.com/5940270/mars-rover-landing-perseverance/#:~:text=The%20Perseverance%20rover%20successfully%20landed,spanning%20at%20least%20two%20Earth)).

- **Ingenuity’s First Flight (Apr. 19, 2021):** NASA’s Ingenuity helicopter became the first aircraft to achieve powered flight on another planet, hovering briefly about 3 m above the Martian surface and proving that controlled flight is possible in Mars’ thin atmosphere ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/04/19/nasa-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-first-flight#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Ingenuity%20Mars%20helicopter%20made,This%20milestone%20paves%20the)).
